-- National Bank of Canada profit falls 13 pct
-- By Sneha Banerjee in Bangalore
-- Tue May 27, 2014 06:02PM EDT
-- None



May 27 (Reuters) - National Bank of Canada <NA.TO>, the country's sixth-largest lender, said quarterly profit fell 13 percent as the year-earlier period included a C$102 million ($93.8 million) benefit.

The company's net income fell to C$362 million, or C$1.01 per share, in the second quarter ended April 30, from C$417 million, or C$1.20 a share, a year earlier. [ID:nCNW5zzhpa] National Bank of Canada said it recorded a rise in the fair value of restructured notes in the second quarter of 2013. Excluding items, the bank said net income rose to C$375 million, from C$352 million a year earlier.